<paragraph blockId="29.[189,1399,1966,2027]" lastBlockId="30.[189,1399,267,469]" lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="31" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
On 
<date box="[233,400,1966,1992]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="1896-05-18">May 18, 1896</date>
, at Mesilla Valley, Cockerell collected, on flowers of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fischer" authorityYear="1979" baseAuthorityName="Cav." box="[1033,1276,1966,1992]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Caesalpinia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="falcaria">
<emphasis box="[1033,1276,1966,1992]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Caesalpinia falcaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, one male and seven females that were used to describe this species. The male of the type series is currently housed at 
<collectionCode box="[311,401,268,294]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/142r-0w94" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="Museum">NMNH</collectionCode>
and was designated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Fox" box="[686,818,268,294]" firstAuthor="Fox" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="63 - 70" refId="ref20698" refString="Fox W. J. 1899. Synopsis of the United States species of the hymenopterous genus Centris Fabr. with description of a new species from Trinidad. Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 51: 63 - 70." type="journal article" year="1899">Fox (1899)</bibRefCitation>
as the 
<typeStatus box="[905,1016,267,293]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The specimen (
<figureCitation box="[1211,1298,267,294]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="30.[189,232,1193,1219]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,697,1152]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[189,1398,697,1152]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="Fig. 22. Centris hoffmanseggiae Cockerell, 1897, lectotype, ♂ (NMNH; USNM ENT 00534200). A. Frontal view. B. Habitus, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1 mm; B = 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3722992" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3722992/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
) has the following data label: Las Cruces Nm [printed]\ on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fischer" authorityYear="1979" baseAuthorityName="Cav." box="[788,1031,303,329]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Caesalpinia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="falcaria">
<emphasis box="[788,1031,303,329]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Caesalpinia falcaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. May 18. (Ckll) [handwritten]\ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1897" box="[189,413,338,364]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoffmanseggiae">
<emphasis box="[189,413,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">C. hoffmanseggiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Type. 
<specimenCount box="[499,521,338,364]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
[handwritten]\ [red label] Type No [printed] 3148 [handwritten] USNM [printed]\ [yellow label] USNM ENT 00534200 [barcode] [printed]\\ DO NOT REMOVE SI DB Reference Not a property tag T. Schultz 
<collectionCode box="[684,774,409,435]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/142r-0w94" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="Museum">NMNH</collectionCode>
[printed]. The females cited by Cockerell were not found during this research.
</paragraph>
